  "slug": "lijiang",
  "name": "丽江",
  "nameEn": "Lijiang",
  "country": "China",
  "population": "1.28 million",
  "coordinates": {
    "lat": 26.8721,
    "lng": 100.2295
  },
  "timezone": "UTC+8 (China Standard Time)",
  "description": "Lijiang is a picturesque city in northwestern Yunnan province, famous for the UNESCO World Heritage-listed Lijiang Old Town with its Naxi architecture and canal system. Nestled between the Himalayas and Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau, it offers stunning natural scenery including Jade Dragon Snow Mountain and the peaceful beauty of Lugu Lake. Home to the Naxi, Bai, Yi, and other ethnic minorities with rich cultural traditions.",
  "coverImage": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1774248382928-e575cbe2f132?w=1200&q=80",
  "highlights": [
    "Lijiang Old Town - UNESCO World Heritage",
    "Jade Dragon Snow Mountain - Stunning peaks",
    "Lugu Lake - Pristine alpine lake",
    "Tiger Leaping Gorge - Dramatic canyon",
    "Shaxi Ancient Town - Authentic Naxi culture"
  ],
  "climate": {
    "type": "Subtropical plateau monsoon",
    "bestMonths": [
      "March",
      "April",
      "May",
      "September",
      "October",
      "November"
    ],
    "avgSummerTemp": "15-25C (59-77F)",
    "avgWinterTemp": "4-15C (39-59F)",
    "tips": "Spring and autumn are best with mild weather and clear skies. Summer is rainy but lush green. Winter is dry and sunny but cold at night. UV is very strong year-round due to altitude. Jade Dragon Snow Mountain is cold even in summer - bring layers."
  },
